'''Kang Min-jae''' ({{ko-hhrm|강민재}}, born 6 August 1985 in [[Seoul]]) is a [[South Korea]]n racing driver. He tested [[Formula Three|F3]] car with the German team [[Mücke Motorsport]] in 2011 [[Hockenheimring]].<ref>{{cite web|title=카레이서 강민재, 독일서 F3 테스트받고 귀국|url=http://sports.news.naver.com/sports/index.nhn?category=sports_general&ctg=news&mod=read&office_id=001&article_id=0005346810|publisher=Naver Sports|accessdate=24 April 2014|language=Korean|date=31 October 2011}}</ref>

==Racing career==
He started his racing career in 2001. He won the kartvil kart challenge championship in 2004. He certificated [[Suzuka Circuit]] Racing School - Formula Basic Course in 2004 and [[Formula Toyota]] Racing School (FTRS) in 2006, Japan. From 2007 to 2009, he fulfilled military duty. In 2011, he won the [[Johnnie Walker]] Keep Walking Fund 2011 in Korea<ref>{{cite web|script-title=ko:카레이서 강민재, '꿈 이뤘다' 1억원 확보|url=http://sports.chosun.com/news/ntype.htm?id=201103300100286290019253&servicedate=20110330|publisher=Chosun|accessdate=24 April 2014|language=Korean|date=30 March 2011}}</ref>  and prepared [[Formula Three|F3]] test drive in October, German.

On 12 December 2011, his documentary about F3 test drive aired by Korean broadcast station, [[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]].<ref>{{cite web|title=MBC스포츠특선, 카레이서 강민재 F1도전기 방송|url=http://sports.chosun.com/news/ntype.htm?id=201112060000000000003585&servicedate=20111206|publisher=Chosun|accessdate=24 April 2014|language=Korean|date=6 December 2011}}</ref>

